vulnerability.name: CVE-2011-1676
vulnerability.cwe: CWE-264 Permissions, Privileges, and Access Controls
vulnerability.description: mount in util-linux 2.19 and earlier does not remove the /etc/mtab.tmp file after a failed attempt to add a mount entry, which allows local users to trigger corruption of the /etc/mtab file via multiple invocations.

vulnerability.name: CVE-2011-1675
vulnerability.description: mount in util-linux 2.19 and earlier attempts to append to the /etc/mtab.tmp file without first checking whether resource limits would interfere, which allows local users to trigger corruption of the /etc/mtab file via a process with a small RLIMIT_FSIZE value, a related issue to CVE-2011-1089.
